China's self-driving tourism market size in 2020 or exceed one trillion yuan
In the context of consumption upgrading and free travel, self-driving travel is encouraged by national policies and more and more consumers like it.
But at the same time, the self-driving travel market, which is expected to break through the trillion-dollar scale, is also facing dual challenges.
In the context of consumption upgrading and free travel, self-driving travel is encouraged by national policies and more and more consumers are loved.
But at the same time, is expected to break through the trillion-scale self-driving travel market is also facing a double challenge, on the one hand, the development of the self-driving travel industry and market demand is not proportional, self-driving tour clubs and travel agencies and other self-driving tour organizers are facing the dilemma of meager profitability; on the other hand, the infrastructure and services faced by self-driving travel are still in the early stage.
60% of the total number of domestic tourists, the market size is expected to break trillions
In 2016, 4.44 billion domestic tourism, self-driving travel accounted for about 60% of the total domestic tourism, by 2020 self-driving travel market is expected to exceed trillion.
According to the statistics of the China Tourism Car Association on the number of self-driving cars, the number of tourists from driving has continued to grow in the past five years, and the proportion of tourists in domestic tourists has stabilized at more than half.
At the same time, regions and countries have shown more attention and support for the emerging field of self-driving travel, and from 2016 to 2017, policies and regulations related to self-driving cars, live cars and camping tourism were intensively introduced.
In July 2017, the National Tourism Administration, the State General Administration of Sports and other eight departments jointly issued the "Automobile Self-Driving Sports Camp Development Plan"; in the same month, the National Development and Reform Commission, the Ministry of Finance and other 14 departments jointly issued the "Promoting the Quality Improvement and Upgrading Action Plan for Rural Tourism Development (2017)", self-driving travel was highlighted.
The introduction of policies has provided opportunities and policy guidance for the development of domestic self-driving travel.
Self-driving club profit is meager, the complete industry chain is the key
Although the domestic self-driving travel market has great potential and national policies are actively guided, the self-driving travel industry is still in the early stage.
According to the "2016-2017 China Self-Driving Tour Annual Development Report", there are thousands of domestic self-driving clubs, car clubs, and carier clubs, etc., but the proportion of tourists self-driving travel accounts for the majority, and the proportion of tourists who participate in various institutions such as car club and self-driving tour club is only about 15%.
At the same time, independent research and development of self-driving travel products online tourism enterprises and traditional travel agencies are also a handful, many online travel platforms sell only some suppliers to provide self-driving travel products, some self-driving travel clubs are also important suppliers.
From the perspective of organizing self-driving activities, it covers many aspects of "eating, living, traveling, traveling, shopping, and entertainment", with a high degree of fragmentation, heavy upstream supply chain, and large random consumption by tourists.
Li Guanjie, founder and CEO of Beijing World Automobile Club, believes that the self-driving club is similar in nature to travel agencies, and the main profit model in the early days is mainly offline activities, and the core point is self-driving tour line products and leader services.
However, now the line products in the field of self-driving travel are seriously homogeneous, the level of service of the leader is uneven, and the self-driving tour club is facing the need to transform again.
It can be seen that the self-driving tour itself is not an independent industry, but it forms a cross-regional and industry ecological circle with its displacement characteristics, and it is very important to form a complete industrial chain.
Experts pointed out that in addition to basic tourism consumption, experience is a more important consumer element.
Therefore, for the development of the self-driving travel industry, the experience characteristics should be enhanced, and the theme of "self-driving travel +" and the IP of self-driving travel products should be developed.
