The NCAA canceled two daily exercises (designed to ease the burden on players), but actually extended their daytime training hours — at least until the end of Friday.
That’s why UCLA’s first three training sessions are scheduled to start at 7:15 p.m. to accommodate the schedule that players have already squeezed.
From canceling training twice a day to more training once a day, the Bears began training almost a week before last season, with Mora training at summer school for the first time in six seasons in Westwood.
